I be sorry for that, for I should often have something or other to give the woman he designed me to work upon. Well (said he) Mirza shall take your directions. Upon saying this <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> called Mir|za to us; Mirza, said the captain, you must observe this person's orders; whatever he commands you to do, you must obey with as much exactness as if you were serving of me. This he told him in the Moorish tongue, but explained it to me in English. Mir|za also told me in French, the commission his master had given him, and farther added, he hoped I would often command him to visit the wine-cellar. I told him we would not want. I advised the captain to let me go to town, to enquire for the still as soon as possible, and to be known to those people that sold drugs.
