<P><HI>I AM something revived at your short sentence I found upon the ground yesterday. I learnt your going to town with the captain, by a discourse between Achmet and Mirza; for I un|derstand the Morisco tongue enough to pick out the sense of what they say; yet I had not ventured to write, for fear my note should have miscarried; if I had not seen you talking to Mirza out of my window. Only consider my time is very short, and if there is no other way to avoid the captain, I must fly to death as my only refuge. Think of it, and farewell. Let me have an answer the soonest, for doubt and expectation are but linger|ing torments.</HI></P>
